<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Syne:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=DM+Sans:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..40,300;0,9..40,400;0,9..40,500;0,9..40,600;1,9..40,300&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"/>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/remixicon/fonts/remixicon.css" rel="stylesheet"/>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/pages/legal.css" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/images/icon.png" />
    <title>Privacy Policy | LinkForge</title>
  </head>
  
  <body>
    <div class="bg-layer"></div>
    <div class="bg-grid"></div>

    <header class="legal-nav">
      <a href="/" class="back-btn">
        <i class="ri-arrow-left-line"></i>
        Back Home
      </a>
    </header>

    <div class="legal-brand">
      <img src="/images/LinkForge.png" alt="LinkForge" />
    </div>

    <div class="legal-container">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-badge">LinkForge Legal Documentation</p>
      <p class="legal-date">Last updated: June 2026 · Version 1.0</p>
      <p class="legal-subtitle">
        LinkForge respects your privacy. This page explains exactly what data we
        collect, why we collect it, and how it is used.
      </p>

      <!-- SUMMARY CARDS -->
      <div class="legal-summary-cards">
        <div class="legal-summary-card">
          <i class="ri-database-2-line"></i>
          <h3>What we collect</h3>
          <p>Email address, click logs, IP addresses on link visits</p>
        </div>
        <div class="legal-summary-card">
          <i class="ri-settings-3-line"></i>
          <h3>Why we collect it</h3>
          <p>
            To run the platform, provide analytics, and keep accounts secure
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="legal-summary-card">
          <i class="ri-share-forward-line"></i>
          <h3>Who we share with</h3>
          <p>
            Only trusted infrastructure providers — Google OAuth, Cloudinary,
            Nodemailer
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="legal-summary-card">
          <i class="ri-shield-check-line"></i>
          <h3>Your control</h3>
          <p>You can delete your account and associated data at any time</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- SECTION 1 -->
      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        When you create a LinkForge account, we collect your email address and
        authentication details. This is required to create and manage your
        account.
      </p>
      <p>
        When someone visits one of your shortened links, we record the
        timestamp, IP address, and click count for that link. This data powers
        the analytics shown on your dashboard.
      </p>
      <p>
        We do not collect your phone number, payment details, or any
        sensitive personal information beyond what is listed above.
      </p>

      <!-- SECTION 2 -->
      <h2>2. How We Use Your Data</h2>

      <div class="legal-list">
        <div class="legal-list-item">
          <i class="ri-check-line"></i>
          <span>To create and authenticate your account</span>
        </div>
        <div class="legal-list-item">
          <i class="ri-check-line"></i>
          <span>To display click analytics on your dashboard</span>
        </div>
        <div class="legal-list-item">
          <i class="ri-check-line"></i>
          <span
            >To send transactional emails — verification, OTP, password change
            notifications</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="legal-list-item">
          <i class="ri-check-line"></i>
          <span>To maintain platform security and prevent abuse</span>
        </div>
        <div class="legal-list-item">
          <i class="ri-close-line legal-list-no"></i>
          <span
            >We do <strong>not</strong> sell your data to third parties</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="legal-list-item">
          <i class="ri-close-line legal-list-no"></i>
          <span>We do <strong>not</strong> use your data for advertising</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- SECTION 3 -->
      <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        LinkForge uses a small number of trusted third-party services to
        operate. Each handles data according to their own privacy policies:
      </p>

      <div class="about-stack" style="margin: 16px 0 36px">
        <div class="about-stack-item">
          <span class="stack-label">Google OAuth</span>
          <span class="stack-value">Optional sign-in provider</span>
        </div>
        <div class="about-stack-item">
          <span class="stack-label">Cloudinary</span>
          <span class="stack-value">Image hosting for logos and assets</span>
        </div>
        <div class="about-stack-item">
          <span class="stack-label">Nodemailer</span>
          <span class="stack-value">Transactional email delivery</span>
        </div>
        <div class="about-stack-item">
          <span class="stack-label">MongoDB</span>
          <span class="stack-value">Database for account and link data</span>
        </div>
        <div class="about-stack-item">
          <span class="stack-label">Redis</span>
          <span class="stack-value">Session and cache storage</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- SECTION 4 -->
      <h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        Your account data is retained for as long as your account is active.
        Click log data is stored and associated with the links you create. If
        you delete your account, your personal data and links are removed from
        our systems.
      </p>

      <!-- SECTION 5 -->
      <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        LinkForge uses session cookies to keep you logged in. We do not use
        tracking cookies, advertising cookies, or any third-party cookie
        services.
      </p>

      <!-- SECTION 6 -->
      <h2>6. Security</h2>
      <p>
        We take reasonable measures to protect your data. Passwords are hashed
        and never stored in plain text. All sessions are managed securely with
        JWT tokens. Account actions such as password changes trigger email
        notifications so you are always informed of activity on your account.
      </p>

      <!-- SECTION 7 -->
      <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        If we make significant changes to this privacy policy, we will update
        the version number and date at the top of this page. Continued use of
        LinkForge after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
      </p>

      <!-- RELATED -->
      <h2>Related</h2>
      <p>
        Read our <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a> for usage guidelines.
      </p>

      <!-- CONTACT -->
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about this privacy policy can be sent to:</p>
      <a
        class="legal-email"
        href="https://mail.google.com/mail/?view=cm&fs=1&to=support@linkforge.com"
        target="_blank"
      >
        support@linkforge.com
      </a>

      <hr class="legal-divider" />
      <p class="legal-footer">© 2026 LinkForge. All rights reserved.</p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
